thread.title: Female driver, 38, killed in car wreck east of Washougal
thread.title_full: Female driver, 38, killed in car wreck east of Washougal | OregonLive.com

author: Terry Richard | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Female driver, 38, killed in car wreck east of Washougal
text:
The driver in a single vehicle wreck was pronounced dead upon arrival at a Vancouver-area hospital Saturday afternoon after the vehicle went off the road at milepost 21 on State Route 14, three miles east of Washougal.
The victim was identified as being from Stevenson, Wash., but further identification was awaiting notification of next of kin, according to the report from the Washington State Patrol.
The single vehicle involved was a 2013 black Jeep Wrangler. The police report said the vehicle was traveling westbound on S.R. 14 when it left the roadway to the right. The driver overcorrected, according to police, and the vehicle struck the eastbound guardrail. The vehicle rolled and the driver was ejected.
The victim was not wearing a seatbelt, according to the police report. The cause of the wreck is under investigation.
-- Terry Richard
